Greenland has reduced its polar bear hunting quota due to climate change, affecting the bears' habitat and food sources.
Conservation efforts are underway, with lawsuits filed against the government for not doing enough to protect polar bears and walruses.
Listing polar bears as a threatened species could lead to stricter regulations on carbon emissions.
The loss of sea ice is forcing polar bears onto land, posing a threat to their survival.
Scientists are being censored from discussing climate change and its impact on polar bears.
The need for global action to reduce emissions and preserve polar bear habitat is urgent.
